{"id":32035,"date":"2019-06-14T15:52:20","date_gmt":"2019-06-14T11:52:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=32035"},"modified":"2025-03-23T12:06:41","modified_gmt":"2025-03-23T08:06:41","slug":"restrain-tongue-except-good","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/14\/restrain-tongue-except-good\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Speech: Restrain your tongue except good words"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Bara\u2019 reported: A bedouin came, saying, \u201cO Prophet of Allah, teach me a deed that will admit me into Paradise.\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Although you have expressed it in few words, the matter is broad. Emancipate an individual, and free a slave.<\/strong>\u201d The man said, \u201cAre they not the same?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>No, emancipating an individual is that you emancipate him yourself, and freeing a slave is that you help someone else free him. Lend a healthy animal to be milked, and treat your relatives well. If you cannot do that, enjoin good and forbid evil. If you cannot do that, hold back your tongue except to say good words<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 69<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0621\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0639\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064c \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u0651\u0650\u0645\u0652\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0639\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0644\u0627 \u064a\u064f\u062f\u0652\u062e\u0650\u0644\u064f\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062c\u064e\u0646\u06